---
// src/pages/about.astro
// ABG DCD — About the Department

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About DCD" description="Learn about the ABG Department of Community Development — our mandate, structure, and mission across Bougainville.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-eyebrow">Autonomous Bougainville Government</p>
      <h1>Department of Community Development</h1>
      <p class="page-lead">Serving communities across Bougainville since the establishment of the Autonomous Bougainville Government.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-body container">

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Our Mandate</h2>
      <p>The Department of Community Development (DCD) is a principal line department of the Autonomous Bougainville Government (ABG) mandated to coordinate and deliver community-centred social development services throughout the Autonomous Region of Bougainville (AROB).</p>
      <p>Our mandate is grounded in the ABG's commitment to improving the quality of life for all Bougainvilleans — with particular attention to vulnerable populations including children, women, youth, persons with disabilities, and marginalised communities.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>To empower Bougainvillean communities through the delivery of integrated, rights-based social services, evidence-informed policy, and inclusive development programmes that promote community wellbeing, social justice, and human dignity.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Departmental Structure</h2>
      <p>DCD operates through a network of divisional units and district-level offices across all 13 districts of Bougainville:</p>
      <ul class="structured-list">
        <li><strong>Child Protection Division</strong> — Safeguarding children's rights and wellbeing</li>
        <li><strong>Women &amp; Gender Division</strong> — Gender equity, GBV response, and women's empowerment</li>
        <li><strong>Youth Development Division</strong> — Youth programmes, vocational support, and leadership</li>
        <li><strong>Community Empowerment Division</strong> — Village governance and community planning</li>
        <li><strong>Social Welfare Division</strong> — Targeted support for vulnerable populations</li>
        <li><strong>IS&amp;CT Unit</strong> — Information systems, digital infrastructure, and ICT capacity building</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The IS&amp;CT Unit</h2>
      <p>The Information Systems and Communications Technology (IS&amp;CT) Unit is embedded within DCD to drive the department's digital transformation agenda. The unit leads:</p>
      <ul class="structured-list">
        <li>Digital Public Infrastructure (DPI) design and deployment</li>
        <li>Data governance and information management systems</li>
        <li>ICT capacity building for DCD staff and partners</li>
        <li>Development of monitoring, evaluation, and reporting platforms</li>
        <li>Cybersecurity awareness and policy development</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The IS&amp;CT Unit is based in Buka, Bougainville, and operates in close coordination with the ABG Department of Personnel and Industrial Relations (DPIR) and development partners.</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.page-hero {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, var(--color-primary-dark) 100%);
  color: white;
  padding: var(--spacing-xxl) var(--spacing-md);
  border-bottom: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
}

.page-eyebrow {
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 2px;
  color: var(--color-accent);
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
}

.page-hero h1 {
  color: #ffffff;
  font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.4rem);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

.page-lead {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
  max-width: 620px;
  margin: 0;
}

.page-body {
  padding-top: var(--spacing-xxl);
  padding-bottom: var(--spacing-xxl);
}

.content-section {
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xxl);
  max-width: 760px;
}

.content-section h2 {
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  color: var(--color-primary);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
  padding-left: var(--spacing-md);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

.content-section p {
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

.structured-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: var(--spacing-md) 0;
}
.structured-list li {
  padding: var(--spacing-sm) var(--spacing-md);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  transition: border-color 0.2s;
}
.structured-list li:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--color-accent);
}
.structured-list li strong {
  color: var(--color-primary);
}
</style>
